<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-75-1025 </DOCNO><TEXT>Four groups in The Netherlands which are involved in cogeneration arediscussed: companies and industries which have invested in cogenerationin order to save energy, companies and industries which are potentialinvestors in cogeneration, electric power distribution companies, powergenerating companies. Also attention is paid to the role of the DutchMinistry of Environment, engineers and manufacturers of cogenerationplants and natural gas companies. An important factor in the decisionto invest in cogeneration is the natural gas price. This price shouldbe related to the coal price to make investments in cogeneration moreattractive. 2 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>